# Documentation Placement

All markdown documentation (`.md` / `.mdc` files that are project docs, specs, or guides) must be placed under **`.\Docs`** (project root `Docs` folder).

## Rules

- **New docs**: Create new markdown files in `.\Docs` or an appropriate subfolder (e.g. `.\Docs\API-Evaluation.md`, `.\Docs\DataModel.md`).
- **Moving docs**: When adding or relocating documentation, use `.\Docs` as the target; do not create new doc folders at repo root (e.g. avoid `.\SomeNewDoc.md` at root).
- **Exceptions**: Cursor rules in `.cursor/rules\` (`.mdc`) and repo root files like `README.md` stay where they are. Schema or DB-specific docs may remain in `DatabaseSchemas\` if they are tied to that folder.

## Examples

- ✅ `.\Docs\MyNewGuide.md`
- ✅ `.\Docs\API-Evaluation.md`
- ❌ `.\MyNewGuide.md` (root-level doc)
- ❌ `.\NewFolder\SomeDoc.md` (new doc folder at root instead of under Docs)
